Core Concept (1 Paragraph)

Two parties enter a trustless agreement. The sender locks GEN into an escrow contract. The recipient activates and completes the task. Upon completion, funds are released or a certificate is issued. If disagreement arises, either party can open a dispute. The resolution is handled either manually by the contract owner or automatically by an AI arbitrator that evaluates the full contextual state of the deal and returns a structured decision.

Deal Lifecycle
create_deal
    |
INACTIVE ─── cancel_inactive ───> CANCELLED
    |
activate_deal
    |
ACTIVE ─── finalize_to_stable ───> FINAL_STABLE (payout)
   |        finalize_to_nft ─────> FINAL_NFT (certificate)
   |
   └── open_dispute ─────────────> DISPUTED
                    |
DISPUTED ─── resolve (AI / owner) ───> CANCELLED | FINAL_STABLE
State Machine
State	Name	Description
0	INACTIVE	Deal created, not activated
1	ACTIVE	Work in progress
2	FINAL_NFT	Completed as certificate
3	FINAL_STABLE	Completed with payout
4	CANCELLED	Cancelled or refunded
5	DISPUTED	Under resolution
Economic Model
Parameter	Description
deal_deposit	Locked GEN (value - activation fee)
base_activation_fee	Entry fee paid at creation
global_value_multiplier_bps	Value scaling factor (10000 = 1.0x)
transform_fee_bps	Fee taken on payout execution

⚠️ All values are denominated in wei
1 GEN = 10¹⁸ wei

Dispute Resolution Model

Disputes can be opened by either party during INACTIVE or ACTIVE states.

Flow
Dispute is opened with reason
Counterparty responds
Resolution is triggered after dispute window
Manual Resolution (Owner)
resolve_dispute_owner(deal_id, send_to_recipient, note)
Owner decides final outcome
Stores resolution note on-chain
AI Resolution (GenLayer Model)
resolve_dispute_ai(deal_id)

An AI arbitrator receives:

sender / recipient addresses
deposit amount
both dispute arguments
off-chain reference metadata

Returns structured JSON:

{
  "decision": "sender_refund" | "release_to_recipient",
  "explanation": "..."
}

Result is stored in:

deal_resolution_note
